<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-06-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-06-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="300" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d300">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Squiers</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-06-13"><hi rend="italic">June 13,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hay states that the Department has been advised that a Ward Line
                            steamer is detained at Habana with Chinese, and instructs Mr. Squiers to
                            suggest to Cuban Government that it would be reasonable not to consider
                            exclusion provision enforceable against vessels arriving upon voyages
                            begun before promulgation of the law excluding Chinese from Cuba.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>